ssful in garnering FTAs with all three players in the global economy: the United States, the European Union, and China. This unprecedented success was built on a strong commitment from three consecutive Korean presidential administrations, each operating within a favorable state-society context that enjoyed the existence of a centralized and effective trade bureaucracy.  aDescription based on information from the publisher. 0aFree tradezKorea (South) 0aKorea (South)xForeign economic relations. 0aKorea (South)xEconomic policyy2002- 4aElectronic books.22aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan)eissuing body,epublisher.40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.8877143